# Network Enumeration Using Nmap

## Objective
The goal of this lab was to perform network enumeration on a target machine using Nmap to identify open ports, running services, and potential attack surface.
---

## Scenario
I was given access to a target machine and needed to gather as much information as possible without logging into the system.

---

## Tools Used
- Nmap

---

## Steps Taken

### 1. Basic Scan (Open Ports)

```bash
nmap 192.168.56.101
```

This scan identified open ports on the target system.

#### Screenshot
![Basic Scan](nmap.png)

---

## Findings

- Identified open ports on the target system  
- Discovered services running on those ports  

---

## Outcome

- Successfully enumerated the target system  
- Identified potential attack surface  

---

## Key Learning

This lab showed how important enumeration is in cybersecurity. Nmap allows you to gather critical information about a system without needing direct access.
